    "body": "## Summary\r\nThis PR fixes a bug in `BatchPrefillWithPagedKVCacheWrapper.forward_return_lse()` where `k_scale` and `v_scale` were incorrectly passed as positional arguments instead of keyword arguments to `run_return_lse()`.\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\nThe method uses `functools.partialmethod(run, return_lse=True)`, which still expects keyword-only arguments for `k_scale` and `v_scale`. Passing them positionally resulted in silent misbehavior or potential runtime errors.\r\n\r\n## Fix\r\nUpdated the call to use keyword arguments:\r\n```python\r\nreturn self.run_return_lse(q, paged_kv_cache, k_scale=k_scale, v_scale=v_scale)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\nAdded regression test test_kv_scale_forwarding_effect in tests/test_batch_prefill.py\r\nVerified test passes for both float16 and bfloat16 dtypes\r\nNo breaking changes introduced\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n- Bug fixed\r\n- Regression test added\r\n- All tests pass locally\r\n- No breaking changes",
